{
  "texts": [
    "Systems like TPMS can address the limitations of simpler keyword-based reviewer matching tools, thus offering high potential for AI automation.",
    "The second stage, i.e., peer review, typically involves the assessment of four main criteria i.e., relevance or scope, rigor or soundness, novelty or originality, and significance or importance.",
    "This is followed by writing the review report (for reviewers) and integrating reports (for editors).",
    "Assessment of a submission's scope and relevance can be assisted through text summarization tools such as UNSILO and more recently GPT-4.",
    "foot_4 However, these still require editorial judgment to review the text summaries against the publication outlets' scope and domain (Susarla et al., 2023), thus offering medium potential for AI automation."
  ]
}